</span><hr size=1> Everyone says that MT is the best newbie zone.  I'd say it's the EASIEST zone, but not the best.  Lots of low mobs without wandering big bad ones, close guards, an NPC that gives out a free container, and places to sell (though for better prices you still want to go inside RV).<br><br>The problem though is the loot is not good at all. There are no humanistic mobs (skellys, orcs, kobolds, etc.--oh, and bixies just don't count!!!!), so there is no coin being dropped and not items.  Most other zones have some kind of decaying skelly and low level mobs that carry weapons, shields, armor or bags and occasional other good stuff.  <br><br>Everyone rags on SF as a starting zone-- yes, it's more dangerous, but i made bank at newbie levels on spiderling silk (plenty of spiderlings--um... maybe too many) and cracked staves i got from decay skellies.  Kobold camps aren't too high either, and the weaker ones still can drop (or did way back when at least) bags and armor.<br><br>GFay would be the best if it wasn't so crowded.  TONS of orcs of varying levels which drop coin, weapons, shields, and lots of armor to wear or sell.  Plus it's still got spiders and wolves for your tailoring needs.  <br><br>Just my toughts...<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 12:57:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best newbie hunting zone.</span><hr size=1> OK, here's a little secret, everfrost is one of the best newbie zones there is. In the newbie area you can start hunting (solo) polar bear cubs as low as 2nd level, and yes they